Indonesia has significant renewable energy capacity, mainly from hydropower and geothermal sources which currently make up 8% and 5% of total capacity respectively. The government has set targets to increase the share of modern renewables like solar to 23% of total energy supply by 2025 and 31% by 2050. However, analysis suggests Indonesia could potentially achieve its 2050 target two decades earlier by aggressively expanding renewables. As one of the world's largest carbon emitters, rapidly tra

Malaysia has set ambitious renewable energy targets for 2035 and 2050 under its Malaysia Renewable Energy Roadmap (MyRER). Currently, renewables make up only a small percentage of Malaysia's energy mix. However, MyRER aims to rapidly increase renewable energy use, with goals for 31% of energy from renewables by 2035 and 70% by 2050. To meet these goals, significant investment and support for the renewable energy industry will be needed over the coming decades. Reaching the MyRER targets will req
The Philippines' $2.5 billion fishing industry could decline 50% in catch and 9% in GDP due to climate change.
In June 2023, temperatures exceeding 40°C in Pakistan led to 22 deaths from heat stroke.

In March 2023, the government revised its 2030 greenhouse gas emission reduction targets for the industrial sector, lowering the target from 14.5% below 2005 levels to 11.4% below 2005 levels. The government also updated its planned approach to achieving these emission reductions, with an increased emphasis on carbon capture and storage technology deployment and the use of international carbon offsets.

The four main priorities of COP28 are: accelerating the shift to renewable energy, changing how climate finance works, making people and nature central to climate action, and ensuring COP28 is the most inclusive climate summit yet.

There are many fun and creative trampoline games that kids can play to enjoy their free time safely. Some popular games include Dodgeball, Monkey in the Middle, Hopscotch, Tag, Reverse Limbo, and Freeze Bounce. Dodgeball involves two teams trying to eliminate each other by hitting opponents with a soft ball below the waist. Monkey in the Middle has players passing a ball while one person in the middle tries to catch it. Hopscotch is played by hopping from square to square on a trampoline grid. T

Philphines has the world’s third-largest installed geothermal power capacity at 1,918 megawatts (MW) – with Indonesia coming a close second and the United States coming out on top.
The Philippines has 1,918 megawatts (MW) of installed geothermal capacity - the world's third largest.

A group of 53 well-known photo editors and experts looked at over 41,000 photos. They picked the best ones in 5 rounds of voting. This got them down to 256 semi-finalists, then 56 finalists. They chose 11 category winners and 1 overall winner for the Red Bull Illume Image Quest 2021 contest. The winners were announced from November 29 to December 4, 2021 on Instagram Live and the website. This was the first time fans around the world could watch the announcements.
